Document: EditorCommandPalette
Path: godot/classes/class_editorcommandpalette.rst
Summary: Methods for adding and removing custom commands in the EditorCommandPalette.

add_command (String command_name, String key_name, Callable binded_callable, String shortcut_text = "None")  
Adds a custom command to EditorCommandPalette. command_name is the display name for the user. key_name uniquely identifies the command. binded_callable is executed when the command is selected. shortcut_text displays the command's shortcut if available.

remove_command (String key_name)  
Removes a custom command from EditorCommandPalette. key_name must match the unique identifier used when adding the command.